<!--
  Sysmon Configuration — Future Integration
  ==========================================
  Sysmon (System Monitor) provides detailed endpoint telemetry that
  standard Windows Event Logging does not capture:

  - Process creation with full command line (Event ID 1)
  - Network connections with source process name (Event ID 3)
  - File creation time changes (Event ID 2)
  - Driver/image loads (Event IDs 6, 7)
  - Remote thread creation (Event ID 8)
  - Raw disk access (Event ID 9)
  - Process access (Event ID 10)
  - File creation (Event ID 11)
  - Registry events (Event IDs 12, 13, 14)
  - Named pipe events (Event IDs 17, 18)
  - WMI events (Event IDs 19, 20, 21)
  - DNS queries (Event ID 22)

  INSTALL:
  --------
  1. Download from: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sysinternals/downloads/sysmon
  2. Extract ZIP
  3. Open CMD as Administrator:
     Sysmon64.exe -accepteula -i sysmon-config.xml

  UNINSTALL:
  ----------
  Sysmon64.exe -u

  RECOMMENDED CONFIG:
  -------------------
  Use the SwiftOnSecurity config as a starting point:
  https://github.com/SwiftOnSecurity/sysmon-config

  WAZUH INTEGRATION:
  ------------------
  Add to ossec.conf on the Windows agent:

  <localfile>
    <location>Microsoft-Windows-Sysmon/Operational</location>
    <log_format>eventchannel</log_format>
  </localfile>

  This config will be populated in a future lab update.
-->

